00:13:04.990 --> 00:13:06.980
It's just basically the
angle of your torso

00:13:06.980 --> 00:13:08.210
compared to the ground.

00:13:08.210 --> 00:13:10.450
And then each arm compared
to the torso.

00:13:10.450 --> 00:13:15.320
So we just get three angles
that are being sent to the

00:13:15.320 --> 00:13:18.460
control node at as fast
of a frame rate as

00:13:18.460 --> 00:13:19.460
the thing can capture.

00:13:19.460 --> 00:13:21.760
And so then the control
node integrates that.

00:13:21.760 --> 00:13:24.220
I've got a way of normalizing
input so I can play off of the

